<section id="prevention">
    <h2>Blood Clot Prevention Strategies</h2>

    <h3>Address the Root Cause: Metabolic Health</h3>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Reverse insulin resistance:</strong> Time-restricted eating, low-carb approach</li>
        <li><strong>Reduce visceral fat:</strong> Belly fat directly produces clotting factors</li>
        <li><strong>Control inflammation:</strong> Eliminate seed oils and processed foods</li>
        <li><strong>Optimize blood sugar:</strong> Keep glucose stable throughout the day</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Lifestyle Interventions</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Move regularly:</strong> Don't sit for more than 1-2 hours without moving</li>
        <li><strong>Stay hydrated:</strong> Dehydration thickens blood</li>
        <li><strong>Don't smoke:</strong> Smoking dramatically increases clot risk</li>
        <li><strong>Maintain healthy weight:</strong> Obesity is a major risk factor</li>
        <li><strong>Manage stress:</strong> Chronic stress promotes inflammation</li>
        <li><strong>Sleep well:</strong> Poor sleep increases inflammatory markers</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>During High-Risk Situations</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Long flights:</strong> Walk hourly, stay hydrated, wear compression socks</li>
