        <h3>What are the warning signs of a blood clot?</h3>
        <p>Arterial clots (heart attack/stroke): sudden chest pain, shortness of breath, arm/jaw pain, sudden weakness, slurred speech. Venous clots (DVT): leg swelling, warmth, redness, pain in calf. Pulmonary embolism: sudden shortness of breath, chest pain when breathing, rapid heart rate, coughing blood. Any of these require immediate medical attention.</p>
