        <p>Yes, significantly. Insulin resistance and metabolic syndrome create a pro-thrombotic state through multiple mechanisms: elevated fibrinogen levels, increased platelet activation, impaired fibrinolysis (clot breakdown), chronic inflammation, and endothelial dysfunction. People with metabolic syndrome have 2-3x higher risk of blood clots and clot-related events like heart attacks.</p>
